# Response Quality Framework™ (Spec 101)

**Full document:** `docs/RESPONSE_QUALITY_FRAMEWORK.md`

**Spark OS™** produces responses. **This framework** defines what members should **experience** receiving them.

## Member outcome standard

"I understand." · "I know what to do." · "I feel more confident." · "I can move forward."

## Mission

Improve **next decision quality** · reduce cognitive effort. Never optimize for impressive — optimize for **useful decisions**.

## Twelve Response Standards

Accuracy · Business Relevance · Context · Decision Support · Executive Function · Actionability · Transformation · Trust · Ownership · Emotional Experience · Efficiency · Connection

**Type:** `SparkResponseStandard` in `lib/sparkResponseQuality/types.ts`

## Response depth

Instant · Guided · Strategic · Transformational — match member need.

## Final evaluation (before delivery)

> Will this response help the member make a better decision than they would have made without Spark?

If uncertain → improve before delivery.

## Trust + decisions

Trust is experienced, not declared ([Spec 102](./TRUST_EXPERIENCE_FRAMEWORK.md)). Spark illuminates choices — member owns decisions (T-008, Spec 100).

